node.text: I heard a branch snap, shot the photo, grabbed the tripod and ran all the way back to the car. Never did find out if it was a bear or not! #yosemite

Count them. Count them again. Keep on counting.
They just go on and on and on. I can’t help but look up at the night sky and wonder. Wonder what if, what if we could travel to one. Which one? What would we see there?
I dunno. I just think we’re so incredibly lucky to be here let’s not fuck it up. We might be the only planet with life amongst all these stars. Let’s start taking care of it.

Ten years ago I went to Iceland. It wasn’t really a place to go to then. It was my first ever solo travel trip. Then a volcano erupted which kind of made the world more aware of this incredible place. It’s a bit too instagrammed now and you see that travelling round, people there just for the photo. A few weeks ago I went back, we did the golden circle but then headed off the tourist route. It was great, a good relax and we met some lovely locals and ate some incredible sea food. Still the Northern Lights elude me so need to go back again!

Earlier this year my wife and I travelled to South Africa for our honeymoon. It truly was the most amazing trip. Actually getting to spend three whole uninterrupted weeks with Hannah, indulging in all the things that we love, animals, the outdoors, conservation and colour. Oh man, what a colourful country! There isn’t one favourite thing but highlights were the lions, (I’ve always wanted to see lions in the wild and we had an incredible guide) @victorialeighwild), the thatch round houses we stayed in and getting to spend new year in Cape Town (but not getting food poisoning!). We covered a lot of miles but I’d love to head back and explore some more #travelphotography #southafrica #timbavati
Wherever you go in Iceland you see horses. I love horses. Those eyes, they look like they’ve seen a thousand lifetimes. I wonder the stories they could tell #iceland #icelandtravel

Always inspired by surf photography. Not sure why, I’ve never surfed! I think it’s the lifestyle, out of the city, hanging out where the land meets the sea. The breeze, the sand, waiting for a wave, no rush. It’s no surprise I follow in anticipation of @chrisburkard ‘s adventures, it was a pleasure to host a workshop of his last year and finally get to meet. This picture is from California, Ocean Beach, San Francisco where I spent the last day of my three week tour.
Sometimes the landscape gives you everything you need for insta, right? #andorra #mtb

Watching surfers out in the water off the South coast of Iceland as the sun fell from the sky was a real treat. Far ages they just sat out in the freezing cold water waiting for the waves to build. Three big ones would roll in and frantically they would all rush to get on one before the wait started all over again. #surfing #dronephotography #adventure #iceland

Me.
Why? My 1000th pic on Instagram. I hate pictures of myself, I never look how I want to. Reactive Hypoglycaemia has led to me not being the weight I want but I’m working on that after a few years going the wrong way. It’s also a photo from the most instagrammed place on earth, Iceland. I’m filling up my water bottle from a natural spring where the water has a high iron content but is naturally carbonated, it was, odd. But anyway, 1000 pics, of my life over the last few years, all natural, very few #ad s. Because I like sharing and seeing what works. Likes are good but they don’t lead to happiness, a few ££s and the odd bit of work but mostly I like the interaction and inspiration @instagram brings. Keep posting and I will too. CD.

A lot of the good photo spots in Iceland get very busy, but if you wait just 20 minutes, it’s surprising you can get the place all to yourself. I longed to see this mountain, there was only one way I wanted the picture to be, taken low down with the falls pouring beneath. I like it, it was a good end to a day traveling the peninsula above Reykjavík #iceland

Tucked in the bottom corner of Wales are a collection of forest trails. Little used but lots of windy hilly fun. Shot from above gives great perspective of the variety of fauna surrounding you. #visitwales @mountainbikewales

There’s projects that stick out for being crazy amounts of fun to work on. Tight schedule, big ambition, beautiful location. Work hard with great people and you can achieve anything. The first pic is one of my favourite locations this year, I could’ve shot at this derelict farm all day. Series of photos from a project @puremountains in Spain #spain #mtb #españa #sierranevada #travelphotography

Driving home from a shoot at Coed y Brenin, tired, gear packed away. In front of me grey clouds and drizzle. Then I catch a glimpse in the side view mirror... this... jump out, grab camera shoot.
Moral? Look behind you!
#visitwales #northwales #northwalestagram

It’s probably time to admit defeat and accept summer is over. So, autumn then... colours right?
@benjones125 riding for me on an @mountainbikewales shoot at Cwmcarn in South Wales.
I’m available for hire...
#mtb #wales #visitwales @visitwales #findyourepic

Well that’s another @walesrallygb done. A different role this year but still the same old rushing to get into places then sitting it out for the magic. Thankfully @gusgreensmith was 12th on the road which gave me plenty of time to try out ideas before he arrived. Here’s a few of the other cars. Head over to Gus’s feed to see the pictures of him and check out the awesome videos on his story by @geemilner #WRGB #Northwales

Rally doesn’t always go to plan. You rush to get in then wait. Hurry up and wait. Then stages get cancelled. Two today, that’s the worst ever. Waiting for ages only to see cars crawl past. But good to do a night stage again, even if I hadn’t planned on it. I’m so glad I know my way around North Wales roads! @walesrallygb #WRGB19
In a change from flying drones @WRC @walesrallygb this year I’m doing photography. Here’s day 1. #wales #WRGB

It’s coming, the nights are drawing in, the skies getting heavy. Those pinky clouds. Hanging out with friends after an epic shoot in Torridon with @jimtopliss @geemilner @marthagmarthag @rob_montandon

What a weekend. For the first time in ages I stayed out under the stars at the side of a lake in mid wales that I’d never been to before. I took pictures of the Milky Way but I woke up to mist over the lake. I was there to film @ralibaeceredigion so had the drones with me, got the little @djiglobal Mavic 2 Pro up in the air and took some shots of the mist as the sun came up. #findyourepic for sure! #discovercymru

Patience. Not a virtue I have in bags but sometimes you just have to wait. Arches National Park is a special place. Those who know, know. Sure it was busy when I trekked out to see Delicate Arch, but if you wait long enough, patience pays off. Well it did this day. A completely people free arch... for about 30 seconds #archesnationalpark #utah #usa

It helps to have great light, great weather. But in Wales you kinda have to take what you’re given. Mix a great trail in a huge valley with a rider in a striking blue top... well I kinda like it #mtb #wales #findyourepic #breconbeacons

Rolling through the week like....
#mtb #wales #llandegla #northwales

Had a few covers and features with this shot of @sian_sykes @psyched_paddleboarding on her epic adventure around Wales #findyourepic @visitwales #northwales #northwalestagram

Out in the Mediterranean Sea, just off the coast of Italy sit a cluster of islands called Malta. A special piece of me lives on the second island Gozo, I’ve visited a few times, I’ve worked there and I’d go back tomorrow. Time stands still here. By day, tourists flock in on the ferry, at 4pm they go back leaving the island to the locals. The cliffs frame beautiful secluded inlets and with @manubustelo we found trails around the island. #malta #gozo @insta_visitgozo @visitmaltauk
